Liverpool were unable to defeat La Liga side, Real Madrid, despite dominating majority of the match. The game saw Brazilian wonder kid , Vinicius score the only goal of the cracker.
One of the closest Liverpool came in the game was when Senegalese forward, Sadio Mane hit the crossbar in the first half. However, that could be his last outing for Liverpool.
According to football transfer expert, Fabrizio Romano, Sadio Mané has announced his departure from Liverpool to his teammates after the game they lost to Real Madrid.
Bayern Munich are the favorites to snap up the Senegalese forward as the Bavarians are said to have tabled a figure of around €35m. The AFCON winner has been one Liverpool’s key men in the 2021/22 campaign.


